<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3630.2.10>
    bibo:endPage "368" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "359" ;
    bibo:volume "3630" ;
    dc:creator "Fontoura, Paulo; Lisi, Oscar; Pilato, Giovanni" ;
    dc:date "2013" ;
    dc:title "A new tardigrade Doryphoribius maasaimarensis sp. nov. (Eutardigrada: Hypsibiidae) from Kenya" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220180>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220181>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220182> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220180>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A – D, Doryphoribius maasaimarensis sp. nov. A, holotype (slide No. 5485) in dorsal view (scale bar = 20 µm.). B, Detail of the cuticular ornamentation of a paratype (slide No. 5488). C, Buccal armature of the holotype in dorsal view (scale bar = 10 µm). D, Buccal armature of the holotype in ventral view (scale bar = 10 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220181>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A – D, Doryphoribius maasaimarensis sp. nov. A, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus of a paratype (slide No. 5486): the placoids are focused. B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus in lateral view showing (arrow) the gradual bending of the anterior third of the buccal tube (paratype, slide No. 5486). C, Claws of the first pair of legs of the holotype (slide No. 5485). D, Claws of the hind legs of a paratype (slide No. 5488); arrows indicate the very thin accessory points and the lunule under the posterior claw. Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220181/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.220182>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A – D, Doryphoribius zyxiglobus. A, B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus in lateral view showing (arrow) the marked bending immediately behind the oral cavity: A, a paratype; B, a Chinese specimen (slide No. 4976). C, Claws of the second pair of legs of a paratype. The arrow indicates the well developed accessory points. D, Claws of the second pair of legs of a paratype. The arrow indicates the well developed accessory points. Scale bars = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/220182/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

